# Cursor Rules for L2Gloria Project

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 16 project migrating from PHP, using MySQL database.
The project follows modern React patterns with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.

## Chrome MCP Configuration
Chrome MCP should be configured in Cursor settings to enable browser testing capabilities.
The development server runs on http://localhost:3000

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow Next.js 16 App Router conventions
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer server components when possible
- Use async/await for database operations
